    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-24T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-24T16:00:00-05:00" n="245"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">548.D1/40: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Geneva (<persName type="from">Gilbert</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-24T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 24, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>112. Your 263, October 17, paragraph 3, and your 246, paragraph 1 (<hi
                        rend="italic">c</hi>),<note n="28" xml:id="d245fn28">Neither printed.</note>
                    please indicate informally to Avenol that this Government does not desire to
                    participate in the choice of a High Commissioner.</p>
                <pb facs="0477" n="373" xml:id="pg_373"/>
                <p>Your 263, October 17, paragraph 4, you should informally suggest to Avenol, in
                    the event that an endeavor is made to obtain an American as High Commissioner,
                    that this Government would prefer that the matter be handled under alternative
                        C.<note n="29" xml:id="d245fn29">
                        <p>The three alternatives suggested for obtaining an American High
                            Commissioner were: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <list>
                                    <item>“(A) To ask the American Government if it desires to
                                        ‘nominate’ or to ‘suggest’ an individual;</item>
                                    <item>“(B) To present the name of an American national to the
                                        Government and inquire whether the United States ‘is
                                        agreeable to’ or ‘has any objection to’ his
                                        appointment;</item>
                                    <item>“(C) To offer the appointment direct to an American
                                        national, leaving to him entirely the matter of his taking
                                        it up with Washington if he so desires.” (548.D1/29)</item>
                                </list>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <p>For your information, an acceptance of the League’s invitation as set forth in
                    your 259, October 14<note n="30" xml:id="d245fn30">Not printed.</note> will be
                    cabled to Bern for delivery.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
